### 4. Build and Run the Docker Container

With all the files in place, you can now build and run your Docker container.

1.  **Build the Docker image:**
    Open your terminal in the project directory and run:
    ```bash
    docker build -t disinfo-analysis-api .
    ```

2.  **Run the Docker container:**
    Once the build is complete, run the container with:
    ```bash
    docker run -p 8000:8000 disinfo-analysis-api
    ```

Your FastAPI application will now be running and accessible at `http://localhost:8000`. The machine learning models are included in the image, so it will be ready to handle requests without any download delays.